result.name: Anli Street Restaurant

reviews.text: 3 stars is already a good rating from me. There are two Anli street restaurants opposite each other. The one which is adjacent to a temple is a better one to me. Famous dish is beef brisket, fish ball, fish cake in soup noodle.

This is one of the most famous noodles shop in Hong Kong.  Their popular dishes include beef brisket noodles with soup, fish balls and slices noodles, deep fried fish skin, Hong Kong style french toast, toast with lots of butter and condensed milk.  Their soup is tasty, won’t leave a sticky texture on your tongue that’s not going away like most other noodles do.  It’s absolutely a must to try.
The two On Lee are from the same origin. both are equally good. Preference depends on your personal taste
Good place for fish ball
